The food services market in India was expected to around 48 billion$ and is now expected to be around 78 billion$ which would one of our user/customers.
The exotic vegetables market reached a volume of around 322 million metric tonnes which is expected to grow to almost 432 million metric tonnes in the next seven years.
Specifically speaking of lettuce, 558 tonnes of lettuce was shipped from India which is annually increasing at a rate of 50%. 
As more and more Indians which is majorly the youth, with their growing disposable income tilt towards eating out, the market is only going to grow.Also there is an emerging
market for individuals shifting to healthy nutrition of which some of the exotic veggies play a central role.
